issues.body:
Hi,

I am using Redis with 3 servers configuration i.e one master(to write data) and two slaves(to read data) and using Twemproxy for load balancing.

And using Jedis with connection pooling.

Now i doing load testing but i am facing below errors

1) Twemproxy Server connections are not properly closed on time and increased upto double or triple of  request(Like for 10k requests server connections opened upto 30k connections)

2) Getting exception like unable to get resource from pool however my poolsize limit is not exceeded and after one command connection returns back to pool.

Server Configurations :- 

1) 64GB RAM
2) 16 core processor

Twemproxy Configurations :- 

alpha:
  auto_eject_hosts: false
  client_connections: 40000
  distribution: modula
  hash: crc32a
  hash_tag: '{}'
  listen: 0.0.0.0:8511
  preconnect: true
  redis: true
  server_connections: 10000
  server_failure_limit: 2
  server_retry_timeout: 30000
  servers:
  - 0.0.0.0:6380:1
  timeout: 5000
beta:
  auto_eject_hosts: true
  client_connections: 75000
  distribution: modula
  hash: crc32a
  hash_tag: '{}'
  listen: 0.0.0.0:8510
  preconnect: true
  redis: true
  server_connections: 50000
  server_failure_limit: 2
  server_retry_timeout: 30000
  servers:
  - 0.0.0.0:6382:1 slave1
  - 0.0.0.0:6381:1 slave2
  timeout: 5000


Jedis Pool Configuration :- 

public class RedisReadManager {
    private static final RedisReadManager instance = new RedisReadManager();
    private static JedisPool pool;
    private RedisReadManager() {}
    public final static RedisReadManager getInstance() {
        return instance;
    }
    public void connect(String host, int port) {
        try {
        	if(pool==null || pool.isClosed()){
				JedisPoolConfig poolConfig = new JedisPoolConfig();
				poolConfig.setMaxTotal(60000);
				poolConfig.setTestOnBorrow(true);
				poolConfig.setTestOnReturn(true);
				poolConfig.setMaxIdle(3000);
				poolConfig.setMinIdle(100);
				poolConfig.setTestWhileIdle(true);
				poolConfig.setNumTestsPerEvictionRun(10);
				poolConfig.setTimeBetweenEvictionRunsMillis(10000);
				pool = new JedisPool(poolConfig, host, port);
        	}
		} catch (Exception e) {
			e.printStackTrace();
			throw e;			
		}
    }
    public void releasePool() {
        try {
			if(pool!=null&&!pool.isClosed()){
				pool.destroy();
				}
		} catch (Exception e) {
			e.printStackTrace();
			throw e;
		}
    }
    public Jedis getJedis() {
        return pool.getResource();
    }

	public void returnJedis(Jedis jedis) {
    	try {
			if(jedis!=null&jedis.isConnected()){
				jedis.disconnect();
				jedis.close();
			}
		} catch (Exception e) {
			e.printStackTrace();
			throw e;
		}
    }
}

Nutcracker-web :- 

![nutcracker-web](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/22707039/22018052/ebaf5d92-dcd2-11e6-91c6-463af69e960a.jpg)

Please help to resolve the issue.

